From 63b1e68f87be151d62e3f3279e7f45ce7f99117d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ekane bryan <ekanebryan5@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 04:47:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf: on-demand image thumbnails + route-chunk prefetch on
 hover
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Thumbnails (backend):
- GET /api/img?path=...&w=... — on-demand resize via intervention/image,
  cached on the public disk, served with immutable headers. Defensive:
  falls back to the original on ANY failure (GD missing, bad image, etc.).
  Uploads are untouched.
- composer.json: add intervention/image ^3.0 (composer install on Railway).
Frontend:
- srcset on EventCard, RecommendedEventCard, event gallery — browser picks
  400/800/1200px variant per slot instead of the full original (~2MB → ~100KB).
Prefetch (frontend):
- PrefetchLink: warms the destination route chunk on hover/focus/touch so
  navigation feels instant. Applied to event/recommended cards → details
  (warms the 153KB map chunk during hover).
